<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-312-105  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 312 105.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Byte  January 1989 v14 n1 p343(7).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>What lies ahead. (prognostication about the future by computerindustry veterans)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Minsky, Marvin; Kilby, Jack; Hopper, Grace; Ritchie, Dennis; Mori,Ryoichi; Kurzweil, Raymond; Feldman, Jerome; Winograd, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several pioneers and visionaries of computer science provide theirprognostications about what they think lies ahead, in the areas ofexpertise, and in computer science at large.andP;  Those contributinginclude Marvin Minsky, a pioneer in the field of artificialintelligence; Jack Kilby, inventor of the integrated circuit;Grace M. Hopper, creator of the first compiler; Dennis Ritchie,codesigner of the UNIX operating system and the C programminglanguage; Ryoichi Mori, a leader in the Japanese microelectronicsindustry; Ray Kurzweil, who played a crucial role in thedevelopment of digital synthesis of music and sound; JeromeFeldman, the man called the 'father of connectionism'; TerryWinograd, a leading investigator in the field of natural languageprocessing; and Charles Simonyi, a chief architect of applicationsat Microsoft.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Computer industry.andO;Feature:   illustrationphotograph.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>